theorem Topology.interior_diff_eq {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A \ B : Set X) = interior A \ closure B := by
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction
    intro x hxDiff
    -- `x ∈ interior A`
    have hxIntA : x ∈ interior A := by
      -- `A \ B ⊆ A`
      have hSub : (A \ B : Set X) ⊆ A := fun y hy => hy.1
      exact (interior_mono hSub) hxDiff
    -- Show `x ∉ closure B`
    have hxNotClB : x ∉ closure B := by
      intro hxClB
      -- Since `x ∈ interior (A \ B)`, the open set `interior (A \ B)` contains `x`
      -- and is disjoint from `B`, contradicting `x ∈ closure B`.
      have hNonempty :
          ((interior (A \ B : Set X)) ∩ B : Set X).Nonempty :=
        (mem_closure_iff.1 hxClB) _ isOpen_interior hxDiff
      rcases hNonempty with ⟨y, hyInt, hyB⟩
      have : y ∈ (A \ B : Set X) := interior_subset hyInt
      exact (this.2) hyB
    exact And.intro hxIntA hxNotClB
  · -- `⊇` direction
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hxIntA, hxNotClB⟩
    -- Construct an open neighbourhood of `x` contained in `A \ B`.
    have hOpenComp : IsOpen ((closure B)ᶜ) :=
      (isClosed_closure (s := B)).compl
    have hOpenU : IsOpen (interior A ∩ (closure B)ᶜ) :=
      (isOpen_interior.inter hOpenComp)
    have hU_subset : (interior A ∩ (closure B)ᶜ) ⊆ (A \ B) := by
      intro y hy
      rcases hy with ⟨hyIntA, hyNotClB⟩
      have hyA : y ∈ A := interior_subset hyIntA
      -- If `y` were in `B`, it would be in `closure B`, contradicting `hyNotClB`.
      have hyNotB : y ∉ B := by
        intro hyB
        have : y ∈ closure B := subset_closure hyB
        exact hyNotClB this
      exact And.intro hyA hyNotB
    have hxU : x ∈ interior A ∩ (closure B)ᶜ := by
      have hxInComp : x ∈ (closure B)ᶜ := by
        simpa using hxNotClB
      exact And.intro hxIntA hxInComp
    -- `x` lies in an open set contained in `A \ B`, hence in the interior.
    have : x ∈ interior (A \ B) :=
      (interior_maximal hU_subset hOpenU) hxU
    exact this
